{
  "stem": "2460.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They are coming back, walking back from Czechoslovakia, and they are coming home.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So every day, we ran to the Slovakian border, waiting for them.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Me, my brother, and the friends.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were running, waiting for them, because we were told that they are walking home.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They didn't give them transportation.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But one day they really arrived.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were happy.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Disappointed, but happy that they came home.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they came home, you know, very dirty looking.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And because they were walking for so long, probably weeks, from somewhere in Slovakia.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they were-- even though my father was Slovakian, but they-- they didn't give them help in Slovakia because they were considered Hungarians.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But they came home.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And my father, because he was a diver, he was-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I don't know if he was privileged, but he was driving even after, driving his trucks between Slovakia and Hungaria.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So this way it started for me, the war.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But we got used to it, and everything was OK.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Even we got used to that-- that our friends are calling us dirty Jew.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "You know, day by day, it was tough.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But the real war started for me when the Germans walked into my town.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And this was in April, Pesach 1944.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
